Actors
QA (Quality Assurance)
RD (Research and Development)
PM (Product Manager)
Administrator
Use Cases
Create Bug (QA)

Description: QA creates a new bug with a summary, description, severity, and priority.
Primary Actor: QA
Preconditions: QA must be logged in.
Postconditions: A new bug is added to the system with status 'Open'.
Edit Bug (QA)

Description: QA edits the summary, description, severity, and priority of an existing bug.
Primary Actor: QA
Preconditions: QA must be logged in and must be the creator of the bug.
Postconditions: The bug's details are updated.
Delete Bug (QA)

Description: QA deletes an existing bug.
Primary Actor: QA
Preconditions: QA must be logged in and must be the creator of the bug.
Postconditions: The bug is removed from the system.
Resolve Bug (RD)

Description: RD marks an existing bug as resolved.
Primary Actor: RD
Preconditions: RD must be logged in.
Postconditions: The bug's status is updated to 'Resolved' and a resolution timestamp is recorded.
Create Feature Request (PM)

Description: PM creates a new feature request with a summary, description, severity, and priority.
Primary Actor: PM
Preconditions: PM must be logged in.
Postconditions: A new feature request is added to the system with status 'Open'.
Resolve Feature Request (RD)

Description: RD marks an existing feature request as resolved.
Primary Actor: RD
Preconditions: RD must be logged in.
Postconditions: The feature request's status is updated to 'Resolved' and a resolution timestamp is recorded.
Create Test Case (QA)

Description: QA creates a new test case with a summary, description, severity, and priority.
Primary Actor: QA
Preconditions: QA must be logged in.
Postconditions: A new test case is added to the system with status 'Open'.
Resolve Test Case (QA)

Description: QA marks an existing test case as resolved.
Primary Actor: QA
Preconditions: QA must be logged in.
Postconditions: The test case's status is updated to 'Resolved' and a resolution timestamp is recorded.
Add User (Administrator)

Description: Administrator adds a new user (QA, RD, or PM) to the system.
Primary Actor: Administrator
Preconditions: Administrator must be logged in.
Postconditions: A new user is added to the system with the specified role.
Manage Users (Administrator)

Description: Administrator can manage (edit or delete) existing users.
Primary Actor: Administrator
Preconditions: Administrator must be logged in.
Postconditions: The user details are updated or the user is removed from the system.
Use Case Diagram in Text
QA Actions:

QA logs in
QA creates a bug
QA edits a bug
QA deletes a bug
QA creates a test case
QA resolves a test case
RD Actions:

RD logs in
RD resolves a bug
RD resolves a feature request
PM Actions:

PM logs in
PM creates a feature request
Administrator Actions:

Administrator logs in
Administrator adds a new user
Administrator manages users (edit/delete)
